# Local secrets for `wrangler dev` ONLY. Copy to `.dev.vars` and fill in.
# `.dev.vars` is gitignored. For PRODUCTION, set these with:
#   npx wrangler secret put APPWRITE_API_KEY
#   npx wrangler secret put REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_AUTH

# Appwrite server API key — console → project → Overview → Integrations →
# API Keys → Create, with scopes: documents.read + documents.write +
# users.read + users.write (documents.* for restaurant/OTP writes, users.* for
# the email-verification flow). NOT databases.* — that only manages schema.
APPWRITE_API_KEY=""

# Shared secret. Put the SAME value in RevenueCat → Project → Integrations →
# Webhooks → "Authorization header value". The worker rejects any webhook whose
# Authorization header doesn't match this. Use a long random string.
REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_AUTH=""

# Resend API key (https://resend.com → API Keys). Used to send the email
# verification OTP. The sender domain (RESEND_FROM in wrangler.jsonc) must be
# verified in Resend.
RESEND_API_KEY=""
